nodes.title: Info
widgets_values:
CLIP L: Keywords & Short Tags. This is the secondary encoder used to anchor the main subjects and simple concepts. Use concise terms here to stabilize the image structure. Focus on physical "ingredients": specific objects, colors, and quantity (e.g., "dog, beach, sunglasses").

CLIP G: Natural Language & Concepts. This is the primary, powerful encoder for SDXL. It understands complex descriptions, relationships, and artistic styles. Describe the scene's mood, lighting, and nuances here using full sentences. Important: Always include the main subject here to connect it with the details (e.g., "A dog wearing heart-shaped sunglasses").

Switch: 1 - Standard Clip G & Clip L / 2 - Both Clip G / 3 - Both Clip L / 4 - Swapped Note: Stick to 1 for the intended SDXL behavior. Swapping them usually degrades quality.
